The Biden-Harris Administration held a listening session to discuss workplace emergency savings programs and employer matches for employee student loan payments. Public policy groups and businesses reviewed the benefits of these programs, including improved financial resilience and wealth accumulation for workers. The Department of Treasury, IRS, and Department of Labor provided updates on interpretative guidance for these programs. Financial services firms discussed their plans for developing and supporting benefit programs for employers. The session aimed to reduce complexity and administrative burden while ensuring consumer protections. The Biden-Harris Administration is focused on improving the financial resilience of American families through various initiatives, including retirement savings protections and student loan relief.